data.description:
The true potential of this property has not been fully utilized- It could be converted to 4 bedrooms, and renovated pictures show the potential of an amazing backyard and a pool, similar to what neighbors did, or by extending the deck/adding a deck on upper level. Views are incredible from this unique property at Guard Gated La Reserve community. Appraised at $980,000 and most properties are valued above $1,100,000 in this subdivision. Great value now and with the potential to remodel this home to YOUR taste and build equity! HIGH 12 ft ceilings, Pella windows and doors, travertine floors throughout. See photoshopped image for ideas on adding a pool in the unused part of the sloped backyard. NEW water heater just installed. 3 wall mount TVs can convey with home. Completely remodeled in in 2006, and lower deck added. If extended, it could be a huge and fantastic outdoor living space. 
Driveway is not hard to navigate, See video attached on how easy it is. If no access to MLS links, Call listing agent for all videos about the property and community. 
Very flexible floor plan -Primary suite is on the Main level with a private deck with heavenly views to enjoy waking up to and to relax on. Downstairs has a second suite w/walk in closet and bathroom. 3rd bedroom has been converted to a Great Room, and by adding a simple door, it could be a THIRD SUITE (has half bath and walk in closet)Travertine floors throughout, solid 8' wood doors, unique tile work, modern kitchen, built in surround sound system in family room and spa like primary bathroom are all in linewith a luxurious feel in the home. Large primary bathroom boasts a huge walk in shower, a jacuzzi tub with a window to desert landscaping. Elegantly remodeled chefs kitchen has floor to ceiling wood cabinets with ton of storage, GE Monogram stainless steel 48'' refrigerator, and oven with warming drawer & microwave, Dacor gas range. Laundry Room has matching cabinets with lots of extra storage and a sink perfecting the space.
No Pool: no problem, no maintenance - the Hilton Resort is minutes away, and monthly membership is only $120 (for singles and $150 for couples) to use the amazing Pools and Fitness center and facilities with special member only events and treats! Golf and Tennis is also at the Resort. AZ living at its best!
Buyers to verify square footage if its important to them
Unique black marble coffee table and the vintage desk by famous Leon Rosen (1970's) is valued between $7,000-15,000 - the ultimate executive desk and a true statement piece. May be purchased on a separate bill of sale for a reasonable price. 
Fidelity Home Warranty with highest level coverage is already purchased and will transfer to buyers
